entries.femaleVariant: No man, woman or child can escape themself.
Yes – place metal where flesh once was. Yes – feign that you are meat no more.
But nay – no kind of chrome can stand in for your soul!
Metal… rusts. Meat… rots. While the soul ever calls – desperately, plaintively – "Be warned! Treeeemble!"
Yes, I say unto you, this city bathes in rust, luxuriates in rot.
